/*
 torwebserv.c
 Foreground per-user Tor hidden service helper + embedded HTTP server
 - No command-line arguments; convention over configuration
 - Does NOT create any .html files; default page is an in-memory string
 - Tries to bind 127.0.0.1:8080; if occupied, attempts to SIGTERM the owner, waits, retries,
   and falls back to an ephemeral port if necessary.
 - Writes torrc with the chosen port, starts tor detached, serves ~/www (files) and an embedded index.
 - On Ctrl+C, terminates Tor, poller, and any child connection handlers, then exits.
 Compile: cc -std=c11 -Wall -Wextra -O2 -o torwebserv torwebserv.c
*/

